From the moment I walked into this fine establishment, I knew that I was home. As a recent transplant from a city where I positively haunted the local brewery, Blackbird seems a gem. The beer selection and pricing are good, the frequent live music (often without a cover!) is a great draw, and the patio is wonderful for group outings due to the abundance of games and ample seating.  The highlight of my experiences here, however, is the congeniality and attentiveness of the bar staff. After just a few visits, two of the regular bartenders knew my face and one even knew my typical order. Whenever I come here for a drink and some entertainment, I find that I never feel neglected, and always have a wonderful time.

The music here has never disappointed me. That's the main reason I come here. I prefer to be outside when possible. There's lights strung up, heater lamps, and a ping pong table. You can rent the paddles and balls with your license as collateral.  The video game machines are annoyingly bright and gaudy. They take away from the atmosphere that the music adds to. The lighting is a little dark, and the times that the disco ball has been spinning, I don't think a light shines on it, so maybe it's just supposed to be there?  As for the food, enough friends of mine have ordered the pizza slices to only have it cold in the middle. I wouldn't order anything that needs heated up.
